===Monographs===
* A Partial Bibliography for the Study of Indian Influence on Chinese Popular Literature. Sino-Platonic Papers 3, 1987 [[http://www.sino-platonic.org/complete/spp003_indian_chinese.pdf|pdf]]
* Painting and Performance: Chinese Picture Recitation and its Indian Genesis. Honolulu: University of Hawaii Press, 1988
* The Contributions of T'ang and Five Dynasties Transformation Texts (pien-wen) to Later Chinese Popular Literature. Sino-Platonic Papers 12, 1989 [[http://sino-platonic.org/complete/spp012_tang_transformation_texts.pdf|pdf]]
* Introduction and Notes for a Complete Translation of the Chuang Tzu. Sino-Platonic Papers 48, 1994 [[http://www.sino-platonic.org/complete/spp048_chuangtzu_zhuangzi.pdf|pdf]]
* The Linguistic and Textual Antecedents of The Sutra of the Wise and the Foolish. Sino-Platonic Papers 38, 1993 [[http://www.sino-platonic.org/complete/spp038_sutra_wise_foolish.pdf|pdf]]
* A Medieval, Central Asian Buddhist Theme in a Late Ming Taoist Tale by Feng Meng-lung.  Sino-Platonic Papers 95, 1999
===Articles===
* Scroll Presentation in The T'ang Dynasty. HJAS 38.1 (1978): 35-60
* Li Po's Letters in Pursuit of Political Patronage. HJAS 44.1 (1984): 123-153
* The Origins of an Iconographical Form of the Pilgrim Hsüan-tsang. T'ang Studies 4 (1986): 29-41
* Parallels Between Some Tun-huang Manuscripts and the 17th Chapter of the Kōzanji Journey to the West. Cahiers d'Extrême-Asie 3 (1987): 41-53 [[http://www.persee.fr/web/revues/home/prescript/article/asie_0766-1177_1987_num_3_1_892|pdf]]
* The Buddhist Tradition of Prosimetric Oral Narrative in Chinese Literature. Oral Tradition 3/1-2 (1988): 106-21 [[http://journal.oraltradition.org/files/articles/3i-ii/6_mair.pdf|pdf]]
* The Sanskrit Origins of Recent Style Prosody. HJAS 51.2 (1991): 375-470
* Buddhism and the Rise of the Written Vernacular in East Asia: The Making of National Languages. The Journal of Asian Studies  53.3 (1994): 707-751
* "What is Geyi, After All?" in: Philosophy and religion in early medieval China. Ed. by Alan Kam-leung Chan,Yuet Keung Lo. New York: State University of New York Press, 2010: 227-264
